The very name of Literature de Curdel has been known since at least June 6, 1865, the date of publication in the Jornal do Comércio of the article “Literature de Curdel” by Theophilo Braga[3]. Places where Literature de Curdel is of great importance are the states of Pernambuco, Alagoas, Paraiba , Para, Rio Grande do Norte and Ceara[4]. A feature of this literature is the presence of regional elements of Brazilian culture and poetic form. Its main social function is to inform while entertaining readers[4]. canons, since their works include folk language and themes.